quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And among them are some who look at you, but can you guide the blind when they will not see"
  10,44,Indeed God will not deal unjustly with people. It is the people who wrong their own selves
  10,45,"One day He will gather them together as if they had stayed but an hour of a day. They will recognize each other. Surely those will be lost who denied the meeting with God, and refused to receive true guidance"
  10,46,"Whether We show you some part of what We promise them, or We take your soul beforehand, in any case, to Us is their return. And God is witness to all that they do"
  10,47,"For every people is a messenger, and when their messenger comes, the matter will be judged between them with justice, and they will not be wronged"
  10,48,"They say, “When will this promise come to pass, if you speak the truth?”"
  10,49,"Say, “I have no power over any harm or profit even to myself, except as God wills. To every people is a term appointed. When their term is reached, not an hour can they delay it or advance it.”"
  10,50,"Say, “Do you see that if His punishment should come to you by night or by day, what portion of it would those who are corrupt wish to hasten"
  10,51,"“Would you then believe in it at last, when it actually comes to pass as you wanted to hasten it?”"
  10,52,"“Then it will be said to the wrongdoers, ‘Taste the enduring punishment. You get only the reward you earned.’ ”"
  10,53,"They ask you, “Is that true?” Say, “Yes, by my Lord, it is true, and you cannot escape it.”"